        {
          "id": "d",
          "text": "Start IV fluids rapidly"
        }
      ],
      "correctAnswerId": "b",
      "rationale": "This patient is unstable (hypotension + hypoxia). Priority follows ABCs (Airway, Breathing, Circulation). Oxygenation comes first. Positioning improves lung expansion. ECG is important but not before stabilizing airway/breathing.",
